<!--69-->Goblin Domain x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok I took a look at the card Depart and thought it was a great card, so I decided<br />
to make a deck around it.  <br />
<br />
Start of Game:  Bid 5-7 depending if you know what they are playing.  Use your<br />
site to pull Sam and begin pulling off Burdens but dont fully exert Sam because<br />
of A Promise.  If you can use the Strength of Spirit card to not exert Sam.<br />
<br />
What you Try to do is use depart and then use Gandalf&#8217;s Staff to Cancel the<br />
skirmish.  Then after site 5 use your pumpers to run your butt off to site 9.  The<br />
Allies are for healing while your not at sites 3 or 6.  The deck has a little twilight<br />
denial but not so much that it will have a huge affect for any one except maybe<br />
Uruk-Hai.  <br />
<br />
Shadow side is very easy.  Use your runners and Archers to give your opponant<br />
so much archery that they will fall easy.  Play as much as possible but be careful<br />
for Sleep and Sentials.  <br />
<br />
They deck is kinda easy to play I think but if there is anything else I think of I will<br />
fix my strategy usng the deck edit.<br />
